        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3932459158" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3652397259250300956">This was a re-read from when the book was new. I remember the frisson of a novel that was set on streets that I recognized, that captured the vibe of nearby Greenwood Avenue. Reading it now, how many years later, I have the same slightly dated sense of it as I do the neighborhoods it depicted. They&apos;re all changed now, no more bowling alley, or most of those record stories. Perhaps because I&apos;m older and more jaded the parts that seemed charming read more like fantasy to me now. Hadn&apos;t I been brok</span>
  <span id="freeText3652397259250300956" style="display:none">This was a re-read from when the book was new. I remember the frisson of a novel that was set on streets that I recognized, that captured the vibe of nearby Greenwood Avenue. Reading it now, how many years later, I have the same slightly dated sense of it as I do the neighborhoods it depicted. They're all changed now, no more bowling alley, or most of those record stories. Perhaps because I'm older and more jaded the parts that seemed charming read more like fantasy to me now. Hadn't I been broken yet when I read it? Was I still thinking there would be that Prince Charming who would love me in patient silence for years, and that so many threads would come to overlap? I still do love this book but reading it during a pandemic casts a shadow on its charm. Everything has changed. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3652397259250300956" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
