<div id="review_2883132087" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2883132087" />
    <a title="Eliece" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1384931-eliece"><img alt="Eliece" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514600888p2/1384931.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2883132087?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eliece" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eliece" href="/user/show/1384931-eliece">Eliece</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780802117793" href="/book/show/1989469.Broken_for_You">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2883132087" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9504905239873342343">I liked this book a lot, although not quite as much as I liked her book &quot;Language Arts&quot;. Kallos&apos;s writing is quite extraordinary; her stories are certainly not what one often encounters. Quirky characters, many of whom have had sad lives, but have overcome their heartaches. I do like that Kallos writes happy endings. Hopefully there is still hope for this almost hopeless world.</span>
  <span id="freeText9504905239873342343" style="display:none">I liked this book a lot, although not quite as much as I liked her book "Language Arts". Kallos's writing is quite extraordinary; her stories are certainly not what one often encounters. Quirky characters, many of whom have had sad lives, but have overcome their heartaches. I do like that Kallos writes happy endings. Hopefully there is still hope for this almost hopeless world.</span>
